THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 422A of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto the
2 provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. 1. To the extent that money is available for such purposes, the
4 Division shall establish and carry out a program to supplement the supply of food
5 available to recipients of benefits provided under the Supplemental Nutrition
6 Assistance Program using mechanisms designed to identify surplus food and
7 distribute such surplus food to the recipients at a discount.
8 2. In carrying out the program established pursuant to subsection 1, the
9 Division shall adopt a plan for the program that must include, without limitation,
10 a system to:
11 (a) Reduce food waste using technology to redirect surplus food to areas in
12 which recipients are experiencing a higher need for more affordable and
13 healthier food;
14 (b) Reduce food insecurity for recipients; and
15 (c) Increase access to food for recipients who are senior citizens.
16 3. The Division shall take any action necessary to obtain federal
17 authorization to carry out the program established pursuant to subsection 1,
18 including, without limitation, applying for any necessary federal waiver.
19 Sec. 3. 1. The Surplus Food Assistance Account is hereby created in the
20 State General Fund.
21 2. The Administrator shall administer the Account.
22 3. In addition to any direct legislative appropriation, the Administrator may
23 apply for and accept any gift, grant, bequest, donation or other source of money.
24 Any money so received must be deposited in the Account.
25 4. Any interest and income earned on money in the Account, after
26 deducting any applicable charges, must be credited to the Account.
27 5. The money in the Account must be used only to carry out the program
28 established pursuant to section 2 of this act.
29 6. Claims against the Account must be paid as other claims against the
30 State are paid.
31 7. Any money remaining in the Account at the end of a fiscal year does not
32 revert to the State General Fund, and the balance in the Account must be carried
33 forward to the next fiscal year.
34 Sec. 4. NRS 422A.232 is hereby amended to read as follows:
35 422A.232 1. [Any] Except as otherwise provided in section 3 of this act,
36 any gifts or grants of money which the Division is authorized to accept must be
37 deposited in the State Treasury to the credit of the Division of Welfare and
38 Supportive Services’ Gift and Cooperative Account in the Department of Health
39 and Human Services’ Gift Fund.
40 2. Money in the Account must be used for welfare purposes only and
41 expended in accordance with the terms of the gift or grant.
42 3. All claims must be approved by the Administrator before they are paid.
43 Sec. 5. There is hereby appropriated from the State General Fund to the
44 Surplus Food Assistance Account created by section 3 of this act the sum of
45 $5,000,000 to carry out the program established pursuant to section 2 of this act.
46 Sec. 6. This act becomes effective upon passage and approval.

